# 7. 『昔話』

Saki: A band you'd find anywhere else...?
Shindo: They were a lot like your band, Ms. Tenma...
Shindo: A group of friends from school who got together and started playing music together.
Saki: Huh...?
Shindo: Just like Leo/need, they were discovered while they were still in school and made their debut... They even made quite a name for themselves.
Saki: Wow! That's so cool...!
Shindo: They definitely had luck on their side. However...
Shindo: In terms of skill, it was the bassist and frontman who did the heavy lifting.
Shindo: Obviously, everyone around them understood that, but after they debuted and when it mattered most...
Shindo: They were headhunted... Someone else had the idea of using the frontman and bassist to form a new band.
Saki: Wait, that's...
Shindo: It was a big talent agency that handled many top-level artists, too.
Shindo: There was talk of a massive ad campaign for them, and a spot at a big summer music festival.
Shindo: Looking back, it was an unbelievable offer. What's more, switching to that agency would mean...
Shindo: ...a chance to have their music heard by more people.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: B-But... If they took that offer... The band they made with their friends...
Shindo: They broke up.
Saki: ...
Saki: But... If that were me...
Shindo: The bassist felt the same way as you, Ms. Tenma.
Shindo: They chose playing music together over having their music heard by more people.
Saki: Yeah, so...!
Shindo: However...
Bassist: Ugh... Why...?!
Bassist: Just why?! Our music was supposed to...
Frontman: I'm really sorry...
Shindo: The frontman cared more about having his music become more popular by jumping ship.
Saki: ...!
Shindo: Naturally, the original band broke up. After that...
Shindo: The frontman... Actually, I don't know what became of him.
Saki: Wait, so...
Shindo: In retrospect, I'm sure there were a number of factors, but...
Shindo: His music was recognized because of the band he was in, and leaving probably caused all that to change.
Saki: Oh...
Shindo: Ultimately, that band lost everything.
Shindo: Which is why I... I understand...
Shindo: Wanting to have your music heard by others...
Shindo: ...and wanting to keep playing music with the people you were lucky enough to meet.
Shindo: Being a band isn't about choosing between those feelings...
Shindo: It's about never losing sight of either.
Saki: Never losing sight of either...
Shindo: In that respect, Ms. Tenma, you seem to be doing just fine.
Shindo: So, I believe there's no need for you to feel scared. Not only that...
Shindo: Wanting to stay together and wanting to have your music heard by others...
Shindo: Those feelings are tough to balance, but I believe that balance lies at the heart of Leo/need's music.
Shindo: Also, I decided to start these talks with you because I personally like your music.
Shindo: So, I'm sure you'll do just fine...
Saki: Mr. Shindo...
Saki: (He's right...)
Saki: (We don't need to decide what our “number one goal” is because both of those things are equally important.)
Saki: (I mean, my feelings... All of our feelings... They're a vital part of Leo/need's music...)
Saki: (So...)
Saki: (Then, I...)
Shindo: Oh, look at the time...
Shindo: Old men like me can't help but ramble on, but I hope you feel a little better now.
Saki: I do...
Saki: I'm okay with how I feel now.
Shindo: That's good to hear...
Shindo: Then, see you again this weekend. I'll be looking forward to our meeting.
